<h4>Page Setup Options Box in All Versions</h4>


<p>The <strong>Page Setup Options Box</strong> is the same for all versions of Excel, so let's look at the options you have to use it to customize page margins for spreadsheets.</p>

<p> There are four tabs at the top of the box: Page, Margins, Header/Footer and Sheet. The <strong>Header/Footer Tab</strong> allows you to customize the header and footer.  </p>


<img class="img-wrap style1" src="images/spreadsheets/pagesetupheaderfootertab.jpg"/>



<ol>
<li>If you click on the <strong>Custom Header</strong> or <strong>Custom Footer</strong> boxes, an option box will open to help you create your own Header or Footer. The option box is the same for both.</li>

<li>The four boxes below the Footer space allow you to customize the pages to which the header and footer will apply. The default setting is for the bottom two boxes to be checked.</li>

<li>After you have made your selections, you can click on <strong>Print Preview</strong> to see how the spreadsheet will look when you print it.</li>
 
<li>If you want to print the spreadsheet, you can click on <strong>Print</strong>. </li>
</ol>

<p>When you are finished with your selections, click OK.</p>

</div>
						
</div>	
				

